11-12 May - Spinach and Ricotta Gnocchi

White sauce
- 1   stick melted margarine or butter
- 1/2 cup flour
- 4   cup whole milk scalded
-     nutmeg
-     rosemary

Add flour to margarine - cook for 2 minutes. Add milk a little at a time, whisking while making the addition of milk. Cook until it thickens. Add fresh rosemary and nutmeg

Gnocchi
- 1 1/4 cup sifted ricotta
- 1     cup frozen spinach
- 1/4   cup parmesean cheese
- 1/4   cup swiss cheese
- 1/4   cup fontini cheese
- 2     egg yolks
- 6     tablespoon breadcrumbs
- 2     tablespoon melted butter
-       nutmeg

Mix together and chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour. Between two spoons amke an egg shape and place in a baking dish that has a layer of white sauce. Garmish with tomato sauce and more white sauce. Bake in a 350F oven for 25-30 minutes.